sudo -u <username> <command> #run command as another user
eg. 
sudo postgres psql 
______________________________
sudo -u <username> -s #run shell as another user
eg.
sudo -u jenkins -s
jenkins@comp:~$ $HOME
bash: /var/lib/jenkins: Is a directory
______________________________

Become root by typing a current user password(not a root password)
$ sudo su - # - means switch env.
